A competent person providing supervision shall confirm that â€”
(a) the work is carried out by competent person(s);
(b) the electrical installations or electrical equipment comply with AS/NZS 3000 and are not
dangerous;
(c) all electrical incidents are investigated and reported;
(d) maintenance systems for the electrical installations and electrical equipment are installed,
monitored and kept up to date for safety; and
(e) any documentation for the performance of electrical work is recorded and provided when
required.
NOTE The relevant authority may have additional requirements for supervision.
